Parameter: combat_potential
Definition: Who wins in a direct 1-vs-1 fight using any combat ability available to them — physical strength, speed, technique, pain tolerance, weapons, powers, transformations. In-fight tactics count. Political scheming, social manipulation, and off-battlefield planning do NOT count.

Tier calibration (pseudo-characters as lower boundaries):
[T1]  A person who can throw a punch but has no training and no physical advantage.
[T2]  An average combatant who loses to anyone with formal training.
[T3]  An above-average fighter who holds their own but loses to career fighters.
[T4]  A dedicated fighter with martial arts, military training, or equivalent.
[T5]  A peak human combatant. No unenhanced person defeats them.
[T6]  A being with superhuman physicals, beyond any human regardless of training.
[T7]  A being capable of ranged destruction — energy projection, large-scale attacks.
[T8]  A being that manipulates fundamental forces — gravity, time, space, causality.
[T9]  A being operating at reality-scale or narrative-immune level.
[T10] A being that transcends the concept of combat within their fictional framework.

Return JSON:
{"universe": "{{ universe }}", "parameter": "combat_potential", "sorted": ["T1", ..., "T10"], "unknown": [...]}

All 10 markers T1..T10 must appear in sorted, in order.

